      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GOOD LUCK BABE (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when fifth at Hobart over 340m behind Promises Made (20.63) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to her name from five starts. Worth another chance. CRYSTAL (2) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three on end. Last start was checked in the run and finished second in a Grade 5 at Hobart (26.29). Harder here but expected to feature again. SEATON (3) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (25.95) last time out at Hobart. Form at the trip sound including two wins. Although beaten ran one of the quickest times on the card last start. Can measure up. NITRO DE GOEY (7) can sneak into the finish.",
